From 05c1b9d9cdbc62c18078df3278e95fccc17ac23b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chris Burr <christopher.burr@cern.ch>
Date: Sun, 18 Jan 2026 05:58:48 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 5/9] fix: Sort Configurable properties alphabetically for
 cross-platform consistency

Property iteration order differs between libstdc++ and libc++ due to
hash container implementation differences. This caused test failures
on macOS where properties were printed in a different order than Linux.

Sorting properties alphabetically when printing ensures deterministic
output across all platforms.
---
 .../tests/refs/FullExperiment.yaml            | 132 +++++++++---------
 .../python/GaudiKernel/Configurable.py        |   2 +-
 2 files changed, 67 insertions(+), 67 deletions(-)

